{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Make a joyful shout to God, all the earth!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Sing to the glory of his name!"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Offer glory and praise!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Tell God, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "How awesome are your deeds! Through the greatness of your power, your enemies submit themselves to you.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "All the earth will worship you, and will sing to you; \nthey will sing to your name.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Selah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Come, and see God’s deeds—awesome work on behalf of the children of men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He turned the sea into dry land. They went through the river on foot."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "There, we rejoiced in him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He rules by his might forever. His eyes watch the nations."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Don’t let the rebellious rise up against him. Selah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Praise our God, you peoples! Make the sound of his praise heard,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who preserves our life among the living, and doesn’t allow our feet to be moved."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For you, God, have tested us. You have refined us, as silver is refined."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You brought us into prison. You laid a burden on our backs."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You allowed men to ride over our heads. We went through fire and through water,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "but you brought us to the place of abundance."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will come into your temple with burnt offerings. I will pay my vows to you,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "which my lips promised,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and my mouth spoke, when I was in distress."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will offer to you burnt offerings of fat animals, with the offering of rams,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will offer bulls with goats. Selah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Come and hear, all you who fear God. I will declare what he has done for my soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I cried to him with my mouth. He was extolled with my tongue."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "If I cherished sin in my heart, the Lord wouldn’t have listened."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But most certainly, God has listened. He has heard the voice of my prayer."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed be God, who has not turned away my prayer, nor his loving kindness from me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}